        <headline>Flood Advisory issued April 21 at 11:38AM CDT until April 21 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of Deep South Texas, including the following
county, Willacy.

* WHEN...Until 100 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1136 AM CDT, COOP Observers reported 6.35 inches of rain
in Port Mansfield due to thunderstorms and water over low-
lying some roadways. Between 3 and 6 inches of rain have
fallen over most of the advisory area.
- Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 3 inches are expected
over the area. This additional rain will result in minor
flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Port Mansfield, San Perlita, Port Mansfield Airport, San
Perlita High School and Port Mansfield Chamber Of Commerce.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
